# Festag Apple gray surfaces

Use Apple’s caption/tile gray for neutral surface boxes on white portal backgrounds — the same tone as `caption-container` on apple.com.

## Token

- **Surface**: `#f5f5f7` (Apple light gray, slight blue-gray tint)
- **Surface hover**: `#ebebed` (subtle darken on interaction)
- **Near-black text on surface** (when needed): `#1d1d1f`

In status executive rows, prefer scoped tokens:

```css
--st-ex-surface: #f5f5f7;
--st-ex-surface-hover: #ebebed;
```

## When to use

- Horizontal card tiles (Projektbericht, Projektprognose, executive overview boxes)
- Informational capsules / caption tiles on white canvas
- Alternate cards that sit on `--portal-card` / white, not full-page gray sections

## Do not use

- `#f7f8f8` or other ad-hoc grays for these boxes — they drift from the Apple reference
- Apple gray on dark canvas — keep existing dark tokens (`rgba(255,255,255,0.05)` etc.)

## Dark mode

On `html[data-theme="dark"]` / `classic-dark`, do not force `#f5f5f7`. Keep OLED popup/content hierarchy from AGENTS.md.
